  • org.wquery:wquery:jar:0.6.0-SNAPSHOT
    WQuery

    Description: WQuery is a domain-specific query language designed for WordNet-like lexical databases. The WQuery interpreter operates on platforms that provide Java Runtime Environment and works with wordnets stored in XML files. It may be used as a standalone application or as an API to a lexical database in Java-based systems.

    URL: http://www.wquery.org

    Project License: WQuery License
